SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c01943909
Version: 1

HPSBMA02481 SSRT090113 rev.1 - HP OpenView Data Protector Application Recovery Manager, Remote Denial

of Service (DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2009-12-07
Last Updated: 2009-12-08

Potential Security Impact: Remote Denial of Service (DoS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with OpenView Data Protector Application Recovery

Manager version 5.5 and 6.0. The vulnerability could be exploited remotely to create a denial of service (DoS).

References: CVE-2009-3844

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP OpenView Data Protector Application Recovery Manager v5.50 and v6.0

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2009-3844    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:N/I:N/A:C)       5.4
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

The Hewlett-Packard Company thanks Stephen Fewer of Harmony Security working with the TippingPoint Zero

Day Initiative for reporting these vulnerabilities to security-alert@...com.

RESOLUTION

HP has provided the following patches to resolve this vulnerability.
The patches are available from the following location

URL http://itrc.hp.com

